benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId} - Transfer a bundle to another account

covered: Valid Payload scenarios (TC01, TC02) cover successful transfer and varying parameters.
Invalid Payload validations (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC15, TC16) cover format and value checks.
Authentication/Authorization handling (TC13 for 401) is exercised, along with missing header case (TC11).
Resource-not-found paths (TC06, TC07, TC22, TC23) cover bundle/account existence checks.
Server error handling paths (TC14 for 503, TC24 for 500) and dependency failure scenarios.
Edge cases and input robustness (TC18 empty pluginProperty, TC19 extra parameters, TC20 large payload, TC21 max header lengths).
Regression tests covering common pitfalls (TC25 transfer to same account, TC26 missing optional fields).
Performance and accessibility considerations (TC27, TC28, TC29, TC30, TC31).
gaps: Duplicate submission handling is not explicitly tested (idempotency or repeated submissions).
Authorization path for 403 Forbidden is not explicitly tested (only 401 Unauthorized is covered).
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not covered.
Caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) is not tested for this POST operation.
Comprehensive validation coverage for all payload fields beyond those explicit (e.g., additional unexpected fields) could be deeper.
recommendations: Add a dedicated Duplicate Submission / idempotency test to ensure repeated requests are handled gracefully.
Add a test for 403 Forbidden to verify proper authorization denial when authenticated users lack rights.
Introduce rate limiting tests to confirm proper throttling and error responses under burst traffic.
Add tests validating caching headers or confirming absence thereof where applicable, e.g., ETag/Cache-Control on POST responses.
Expand validation coverage to exercise additional payload fields and unexpected extra data to ensure robust input validation.
